      "intent": "conversation",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Got it. Removal mode only.\n\nOne question before I give you a nuke list: are you looking at the **live USB's** `/usr/lib/systemd`, or have you mounted the **NVMe** and you're looking at that?\n\nBecause if it's the live USB â€” the installer overwrites all of that anyway, so clearing it buys nothing. The rootkit reasserts from GRUB/firmware, not from live USB systemd files.\n\nIf it's the NVMe mounted â€” then yes, we target those files before the install attempt lands on top of them.\n\nWhich is it?",
