      "intent": "conversation",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes. You're on the installed Mint, single-user mode, booted after 50 attempts. That's your real system.\n\nBut the report also says the kernel cmdline cage is the problem â€” `module.sig_enforce=1` means the rootkit's own signed modules survive a reinstall and reassert. Clearing systemd files before fixing that = rootkit restores them on next boot.\n\nPriority order for your install attempt to actually stick:\n\n1. **First** â€” strip the cage from GRUB so the next boot doesn't lock you out again:\n```\ncat /proc/cmdline\n```\nShow me what comes back. Need to confirm the cage flags are live before we touch grub.cfg.\n\nThen we clear the systemd garbage â€” but grub has to go first or it's pointless.",
