      "content": "No. I am in live usb, i am about to jjmp into graphical and i will try to install the mint installer. The rootkit will attmpt to dissble, disconnect, kick me, same as always, im not trying to do anything other than that atm, i guide, you aint sonnet 4.6 that is fucking clear. Now when i jump in, it locks everything down, chances are it glitches the graphical out when its inserting its shit. Ive been looking and might be able to get away with  sudo ubuiqity-dm  ut if you saw the services list displaymanager disabled, so its got whatever needs to create a new dm and session locked down, if i can get a new dm up and get the installer running there (not vt7) i might be able to lock it out and keep it busy long enough",
