      "parentMessageID": "bd1f15ca-edca-4ae7-88b0-a55200ea4135",
      "intent": "conversation",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Right. So the play is:\n\nSpin up a fresh X session on a different VT â€” not VT7, that's rootkit's turf. Run ubiquity inside that.\n\nWhen you're ready, try:\n```\nsudo ubiquity-dm\n```\n\nIf it gets killed or errors, fall back to:\n```\nsudo X :1 vt8 -ac &\n```\nThen:\n```\nDISPLAY=:1 sudo ubiquity gtk_ui\n```\n\n`x11-common` being masked may bite you on the second option. If X won't start, hit me with the error.\n\nGo when ready â€” I'm here.",
